post_text:
Chagrin Falls Exempted Village School District has a new theme and focus this year, “CONNECTED.” This was introduced at the staff’s virtual convocation ceremony on August 17.

"Due to the nature of the necessary public health strategies, this pandemic has caused a great deal of isolation from friends and family. However, we all are aware there are consequences to extensive isolation impacting the social and emotional health of individuals. This is especially concerning with young people. That is why the theme for the upcoming school year is CONNECTED," said Superintendent Dr. Robert Hunt, Chagrin Falls Schools. "Regardless if our students are hybrid or remote, as a District, we are focused on connection before content. We know success relies on the interconnectedness between colleagues, parents and students; and we look forward to working collaboratively to make this a successful school year."

The District will be using the hashtag #cfevsCONNECTED on social media throughout the school year to highlight the ways they are focusing on the interconnection between the school community.

post_text:
Congratulations to four-year CFHS public forum debate partners, seniors Sasha Haines and Maggie Mills. They’ve been together from the beginning and have seen as much as any debaters could dream of seeing. Through their extensive preparation with their coach Richard Haber, they have achieved a monumental feat: competing in the final round of Nationals 2020 for a chance to be crowned the top debaters in the country. I could not be more proud of you, Sasha and Maggie. You are the embodiment of students in the truest sense of the word, and over the course of these last four years you have mastered the fine art of debate.
- Ken Kasee, Advisor

DRONE OHIO is feeling thankful at Chagrin Falls High School.
April 20 at 2:23 PM · Chagrin Falls, OH ·

In support of the Chagrin Falls Class of 2020, DRONE OHIO will live stream tonight's lighting of the football stadium at approximately 8:15pm. High Schools all over the state are doing this as well. So please join us tonight, and as always, be safe, and do whatever you can to help us all through these trying times!

Superintendent Dr. Robert Hunt interviews Director of Technology and Innovation Mike Daugherty. Mr. Daugherty was on the forefront of creating the District's virtual learning plan and we are now seeing versions of our plan emerge around Ohio and even around the country. Mr. Daugherty talks about the process we went through in implementing our virtual learning plan. He also talks about all we have done as a District over the past 5-7 years that really helped put us in a position to implement a high quality virtual learning program. #CFEVS #cfevsHOME #CFEVSGoesDigital

post_text:
One on one with Rachel Jones, principal of Gurney Elementary School and Superintendent Dr. Robert Hunt. Hear how her days are filled with virtual team meetings with building leadership teams, tutors and grade level teams, troubleshooting, answering questions, connecting with elementary principals throughout the state, and most importantly connecting with our students and families. She addresses facing the unknown with moving to online learning with approx. 500 third-grade students and under and how it has been challenging but going so well. She is grateful to her incredible staff who is thriving with new ideas, creativity and enthusiasm. This has made virtual learning take off and she says it has been exciting to watch. #cfevsHOME #CFEVSGoesDigital

https://youtu.be/9QXxnqmFSMw

post_text:
Chagrin Falls High School students Anais and Emily received an opportunity for an invaluable learning experience this upcoming summer. After going through an application process, Levi and Collins were two of the five students selected for Hyland’s pilot high school internship program. Hyland, whose global headquarters is in Westlake, Ohio, is a leading content services provider that enables thousands of organizations to deliver better experiences to the people they serve. This is the first time Hyland is offering an internship program specifically for high school students. In the past, high school students could apply to Hyland’s internships, but they competed against college students.

Read more here:
http://www.chagrinschools.org/protected/ArticleView.aspx?iid=632AP2B&dasi=4G2GI

#cfevsHOME

post_text: Four Chagrin Falls High School students have been named National Merit Finalists in the 2020 National Merit Scholarship Program. These students are Ana Kevorkian, Grace Lee, Parker Broz and Maggie Mills. Over 15,000 of the 16,000 Semifinalists named in September 2019 have met all requirements to advance to Finalist standing in the competition. All Finalists will be considered for National Merit Scholarships to be offered in 2020. Congratulations! #cfevsHOME
